        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21681/2604.21681v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Sapiens2for dense-prediction tasks.We compare 1B models from both generations on segmentation, depth, and normals. Sapiens2 improves over Sapiens with stronger generalization and sharper segmentation of rare classes (lips, tongue, earrings), achieving pixel-accurate hair segmentation. On geometric tasks (depth, normals), it captures subtler facial, clothing, and hair details—all without task-specific architectures.",
                "position": 236
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21681/2604.21681v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:k-NN comparison using [cls] token.Sapiens2learns a more discriminative, human-semantic feature space—grouping visually similar concepts and improving retrieval performance at high resolution.",
                "position": 269
            }
        ]
    },
