    {
        "header": "3Pretraining",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21681/2604.21681v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Sapiens2Pretraining. We combine the masked reconstruction loss (ℒmae\\mathcal{L_{\\text{mae}}}) with a global contrastive loss on [CLS] (ℒcl\\mathcal{L}_{\\text{cl}}). Multiple image views are generated, and a student–teacher framework matches predicted distributions across views.ℒmae\\mathcal{L_{\\text{mae}}}helps the model learn low-level details (e.g.texture) for high-fidelity dense tasks, whileℒcl\\mathcal{L_{\\text{cl}}}improves semantic understanding across human images.",
                "position": 317
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21681/2604.21681v1/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:Windowed self-attentionfor 4K resolution.",
